This application is a Ruby on Rails veterinary clinic system that manages pets, owners, vets, appointments, and treatments, including image uploads and rich text content.

How to run the app

To set up and run the application locally:

bundle install
rails db:create
rails db:migrate
rails db:seed
bin/rails server

Then open your browser at:

http://localhost:3000

This project uses Active Storage variants to process and resize images.
For this reason, libvips must be installed on your system.

Install on Linux / WSL:
sudo apt update
sudo apt install libvips

Trix (Action Text) sanitization note

The application uses Action Text (Trix editor) for rich text fields such as Treatment#clinical_notes.

Important behavior:

HTML input is automatically sanitized by Rails
Unsafe tags and scripts are removed
Only safe formatting (bold, lists, links, etc.) is preserved
This ensures protection against XSS (cross-site scripting)
